fields.draw_shape_text:
Getting Started

Please take a few moments to familiarize yourself with the tool before you start drawing shapes. Brief instructions and demonstration videos can be found by clicking on the "Instructions" tab at the top of this window. These are highly recommended as they will not only help you get started, but show you features that can make this process go much faster.

How It Works

The way the drawing process works is for each species group you target, you are given an imaginary bag of 100 pennies. You will draw shapes on the map representing your fishing grounds and then place some number of pennies on those shapes. The more pennies you place on a shape, the more value or importance you are placing on it. Keep doing this until you have drawn all your shapes and used all your pennies.

How many shapes you draw and how specific you are is up to you. Most people draw between 3 and 8 shapes per fishery per user group.

More Help

To see this information again after closing this window, click the Help button in the upper right. Additional help can be found on our frequently asked questions page. Please do not hesitate to email fish@ecotrust.org if you need more help.
fields.group_status_text:
Please carefully read all instructions and complete the survey. You will be asked to answer questions and draw your fishing grounds. The drawing portion of the survey can be technically challenging for some. Please understand this is a necessary part of the survey and provides the best representation of your fishing interests.

If you have questions about Ecotrust's involvement in the MLPA process and what your incentive is to reveal your fishing grounds to us, please visit our MLPA page.

We are listening to your feedback. If you have technical problems please read our Frequently Asked Questions. If you are finding the online interview too difficult to complete, please email us at fish@ecotrust.org or call us using the number provided in your registration email and we will find a way to get your information included into this process.

fields.answer: The precision of your shapes is important; however, we understand that accuracy will vary between users.  Please just do the best you can with the time you have and provide us with any extra information on boundaries so that our team can make your shapes more accurate.
fields.question: How much precision should I use when drawing shapes?

fields.answer: The number of shapes you draw is your choice.  Most people draw anywhere from 2-10 shapes per resource.
fields.question: How many shapes should I draw?

fields.answer: The map takes the longest to load.  People without a broadband internet connection may need to wait up to a minute or two the first time they draw shapes.  If you wait and still nothing loads then try refreshing the page. If still nothing then verify you are using a supported browser (IE 6+, Firefox 1.0+, Safari 1.2+, Chrome 2+). If you have a supported browser then next verify you have 'javascript' enabled in your browser preferences. Seek the help of friends and family if you're unsure how to do any of these steps or email us at fish@ecotrust.org.  Another option is simply to try another computer. Computers more than 5 years old are more likely to have issues.
